Delek Israeli Soars Most in 31 Months on Delek Petroleum Bid

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-07-13T13:59:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/delek-israeli-soars-most-in-30-months-on-delek-petroleum-bid.html
Delek The Israeli Fuel Corp. surged
the most in more than 31 months after Delek Petroleum Ltd.
offered to buy the remaining 22.8 percent stake in the fuel
distributor for 238 million shekels ($69 million) or 92 shekels
a share.  The shares jumped 12 percent, the most since December 2008,
to 93.64 shekels at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv .  Delek Petroleum currently owns about 8.76 million Delek
Israeli shares or 77.2 percent of the company, according to the
 offer statement .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Susan Lerner in Jerusalem at 
 slerner2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  